In .NET MAUI, use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;

public static MauiApp CreateMauiApp()
{
    var builder = MauiApp.CreateBuilder();
    builder.UseMauiApp<App>();

    builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
    {
#if ANDROID
        events.AddAndroid(android => android
            .OnPause(activity =>
            {
                // Runs when app is partially obscured
            })
            .OnStop(activity =>
            {
                // Runs when app is no longer visible
            }));
#elif IOS
        events.AddiOS(ios => ios
            .DidEnterBackground(application =>
            {
                // Runs when app enters background
            }));
#endif
    });

    return builder.Build();
}
```

**Key points:**
- Use `#if ANDROID` / `#elif IOS` preprocessor directives to keep platform code conditional.
- The `AddAndroid`/`AddiOS` extensions map directly to native lifecycle callbacks.
- Other events are available too (e.g., `OnResume`, `WillEnterForeground`, `OnCreate`, etc.).
